1.\lim_{x\to1}\frac{x^2 - 1}{x + 1}
=\lim_{x\to1}\frac{(x+1)(x-1)}{x+1} = 0
\frac{\frac{\mathrm{d} }{\mathrm{d} x}(x^2-1)}{\frac{\mathrm{d} }{\mathrm{d} x}(x+1)}= \frac{2x}{1} = 2
\lim_{x\to2}\frac{x^3-8}{x-2} = \lim_{x\to2}\frac{(x-2)(x^2+2x+4)}{(x-2)}=4+8+4=16
\frac{\frac{\mathrm{d} }{\mathrm{d} x}(x^3-8)}{\frac{\mathrm{d} }{\mathrm{d} x}(x-2)}=\frac{3x^2}{1}=12
\dfrac{0}{0}
\dfrac{\infty}{\infty}
\lim_{x \to 1} \dfrac{x^2-1}{x+1}
x=2
\dfrac{0}{0}
\lim_{x \to 2} \dfrac{x^3-8}{x-2} = \lim_{x \to 2} (x^2 + 2x + 4) = 2^2 + 2 \times 2 + 4 = 4 + 4 + 4 = 12 \,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\, (\star)
\dfrac{x^3-8}{x-2}
(\star)
\lim_{x \to 2} \dfrac{x^3-8}{x-2} = \lim_{x \to 2} \dfrac{\dfrac{d(x^3-8)}{dx}}{\dfrac{d(x-2)}{dx}} = \lim_{x \to 2} \dfrac{3x^2}{1} = 12
